  "text": "Effect of AICAr on MTX polyglutamate synthesis. For CCRF-CEM cells, the presence of 0.5 mmol/L AICAr increases both total drug (3-fold) and MTX polyglutamate (n z 2) accumulation (3. Fig. 2 ). AICAr does not affect v i under these conditions. After 5 to 10 minutes of linear uptake, influx in the absence of AICAr plateaus, as is typical in vitro (e.g., ref. [CITATION_1] . In contrast, in the presence of AICAr, uptake continues after 10 minutes at a rate dependent on the AICAr concentration; there is little indication of a 30-minute plateau at high AICAr. AICAr at 0.5 to 1.0 mmol/L increases MTX accumulation at 30 minutes by z3-fold. High-performance liquid chromatography analysis shows that ÀAICAr at 30 minutes, 86% of intracellular radiolabel is MTX and 12% is MTX-g-Glu, whereas +0.5 mmol/L AICAr, 83% is MTX and 7.5% is MTX-g-Glu with <1% MTX-g-(Glu) [CITATION_2] (Fig. 3) . v i values (0-5 minutes) are the same FAICAr (note scale change), but AICAr potentiates 30-minute accumulation at 1 to 10 Amol/L MTX, with highest potentiation (6-fold) at 10 Amol/L. The %10-minute delay before onset of AICAr potentiation is seen at all MTX levels. Analysis of v i data shows that ÀAICAr, V max /K t = 0.44, whereas +AICAr, V max /K t = 0.47, suggesting that kinetics at early times are unaffected by AICAr. These V max /K t values are consistent with those expected for the RFC (3, 6). Because rates >5 minutes are not v i , the later portion of the +AICAr curve where potentiation is observed cannot be analyzed by MichaelisMenten kinetics (see below).",
